description: A Late Iron Age and Roman settlement that declined in the 4th CE. A circular building was discovered which has been associated with a shrine.
bibliography: Martyn, Blick, Brindle, and et al. “Kelvedon (Essex).” The Rural Settlement of Roman Britain: an online resource, 2015. https://doi.org/10.5284/1030449.
Rodwell, K. A. “The Prehistoric and Roman Settlement at Kelvedon.” Essex CBA Research Report 63 (1988).
